info.headline: High Surf Warning issued December 26 at 11:33PM PST until December 27 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...HIGH SURF WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 7 PM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...For the High Surf Warning, dangerously large breaking waves of 24 to 30 feet expected in the surf zone. For the Coastal Flood Advisory, minor coastal flooding. * WHERE...North Coast zone. * WHEN...For the High Surf Warning, from 7 AM to 7 PM PST Tuesday. For the Coastal Flood Advisory, until 5 PM PST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding, one to two feet above ground level, is possible around high tide. This may lead to flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong winds could drive waters upward even further depending on where the strongest winds set up.
info.instruction: Everyone should remain out of the water due to life-threatening surf conditions. Stay off of jetties, piers, and other waterside infrastructure.
